                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Klieforth, Alfred W.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Klieforth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-23T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 23, 1945—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 9:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. Reference my 30, June 21. President Beneš through British Ambassador
                    expressed his sincere regrets but added that he was not surprised over the
                    incident. Acting Foreign Minister yesterday afternoon informed me that he had
                    presented the case to Russian Embassy here for investigation.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow as No. 7.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Klieforth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
